34:53.440 --> 34:54.800
Are you allowed to do that?

34:57.880 --> 34:59.760
Why are you here?

34:59.760 --> 35:01.920
Give me your phone.

35:01.920 --> 35:03.080
What?

35:03.080 --> 35:04.840
Give it to me. Why?

35:04.840 --> 35:06.640
You want me to help you?

35:06.640 --> 35:08.520
No.

35:08.520 --> 35:09.720
You do not trust me?

35:09.720 --> 35:12.280
No. Last time I gave you
Father Patenaude.

35:12.280 --> 35:13.800
Yeah. And took a man's eye out.

35:15.360 --> 35:16.960
He was a liar.

35:16.960 --> 35:21.520
And you're not?
Then tell me who you work for.

35:21.520 --> 35:23.640
Someone who wants to keep you safe.

35:23.640 --> 35:25.160
That's, that's not an answer.

35:25.160 --> 35:27.480
It is if you're in danger.
Am I in danger? Yeah.

35:31.560 --> 35:33.040
Who from?

35:33.040 --> 35:35.800
Please, give me your phone.

35:35.800 --> 35:37.720
Why?
I cannot watch you all the time.

35:37.720 --> 35:39.720
Yeah, I don't want you to
watch me at all!

35:39.720 --> 35:41.200
And they know it.

35:41.200 --> 35:42.240
Who's they?

35:44.000 --> 35:46.960
So if someone comes, and they
might...

35:48.240 --> 35:49.360
..you should call me.

35:51.080 --> 35:52.240
This is ridiculous.

35:52.240 --> 35:53.600
Wasn't before, isn't now.

36:01.520 --> 36:02.600
Unlock it.

36:19.520 --> 36:21.760
"A", double "H".

36:21.760 --> 36:23.040
"Ahh"?

36:24.520 --> 36:25.560
Ha-ha.

36:27.000 --> 36:30.800
That lawyer you spoke to
worked for Ganimana.

36:33.440 --> 36:35.120
You are following me.

36:35.120 --> 36:36.160
He's dead.

36:38.080 --> 36:39.160
How?

36:39.160 --> 36:40.200
Dead.

36:40.200 --> 36:42.880
So any trouble?

36:42.880 --> 36:44.160
Call "Ahh". I'm serious!

36:47.320 --> 36:49.280
And stay away from Patrice Ganimana.

37:06.320 --> 37:07.360
Passion fruit?

37:09.240 --> 37:10.760
Maybe melon, do you want some?

37:12.400 --> 37:14.000
So?

37:14.000 --> 37:16.840
So? What do you expect me to say?

37:16.840 --> 37:18.120
Whatever you think.

37:19.880 --> 37:21.760
He's right. Stay away from Ganimana.

37:23.080 --> 37:25.720
He works for you?
Me?

37:25.720 --> 37:28.640
If I had access to an
extra-judicial hit man,

37:28.640 --> 37:30.800
do you think I'd be wasting my
time here presenting

37:30.800 --> 37:34.800
The Infrastructure Projects Team
of the Year?

37:34.800 --> 37:36.560
So whose is he?

37:37.640 --> 37:40.600
My guess, Bibi Mundanzi,

37:40.600 --> 37:46.040
which means the table stakes you're
playing at are pretty fucking high!

37:46.040 --> 37:47.360
No.

37:47.360 --> 37:52.080
No, she wants Ganimana extradited,
why would they want to keep me away?

37:52.080 --> 37:55.040
Unlike you.
I hoped the UN would pick him up.

37:55.040 --> 37:58.320
Well, it didn't work out that way,
did it?

37:59.640 --> 38:03.240
No, it didn't.
So, now it's just down to them.

38:03.240 --> 38:04.280
Them?

38:06.360 --> 38:09.120
Why did David Runihura go
and see you?

38:09.120 --> 38:11.080
I told you, I can't say.

38:11.080 --> 38:12.440
Was it for a file, Michael?

38:14.560 --> 38:20.480
On Patrice Ganimana, drawn up
by Eve, by my mother, in '97?

38:22.360 --> 38:23.600
He came to see you.

38:26.400 --> 38:30.160
He wants me to fly out there
and write a report on the state

38:30.160 --> 38:31.200
of their judiciary.

38:32.480 --> 38:33.520
And you said yes?

38:36.120 --> 38:37.360
Think I just have.

38:39.960 --> 38:41.120
I pay your bills, Kate.

38:41.120 --> 38:42.960
And I think I've also just resigned.

38:45.040 --> 38:49.200
The Rwandan judiciary does not have
the capability of trying a

38:49.200 --> 38:50.640
Transfer case, not on their own.

38:50.640 --> 38:51.800
Says who?

38:51.800 --> 38:55.800
This country, last year -
six - right to a fair trial.

38:55.800 --> 38:57.640
A lot of other countries disagree.

38:57.640 --> 39:00.520
And they're looking to you to prove
the British judiciary wrong?

39:00.520 --> 39:02.920
That's a pretty tall order,
Kate, even for you.

39:02.920 --> 39:06.520
Well, you didn't seem to think so
when you had me working for Alice.

39:06.520 --> 39:08.000
Then you had me.

39:08.000 --> 39:09.520
Out there, you'll be on your own.

39:09.520 --> 39:11.960
No, no, I'll be with people willing
to prosecute

39:11.960 --> 39:13.200
the very man you're not.

39:16.320 --> 39:20.680
I'd like nothing better than to see
Ganimana brought to justice.

39:20.680 --> 39:23.680
If, when he does,
that's what actually happens.

39:23.680 --> 39:26.080
You know what's really unsettling?

39:26.080 --> 39:28.240
It's not just your behaviour,
it's my mother's.

39:28.240 --> 39:31.040
To discover she'd even drawn up a
file against this guy,

39:31.040 --> 39:34.080
but instead of prosecuting
the fucker, she decided to go for

39:34.080 --> 39:37.160
Simon Nyamoya instead, a man who'd
brought the genocide to a close!

39:37.160 --> 39:38.560
It wasn't like that. No?

39:38.560 --> 39:42.400
So why is Patrice Ganimana sitting
two miles away with you

39:42.400 --> 39:44.560
DOING NOTHING TO HELP?!

39:54.960 --> 39:56.320
Where's that file?

39:59.200 --> 40:00.600
You're being played.

40:00.600 --> 40:02.320
Hmm.

40:02.320 --> 40:04.600
Yeah, I think I am.

40:05.600 --> 40:08.040
Stay away from Ganimana.

40:08.040 --> 40:09.840
Says you and your
paramilitary buddy.

40:09.840 --> 40:11.080
He's very dangerous.

40:11.080 --> 40:12.880
Yeah, took a guy's eye out.

40:14.040 --> 40:15.800
Ganimana.

40:15.800 --> 40:19.800
Because of Blake Gaines?
I looked it up.

40:20.840 --> 40:22.520
Suicide.

40:22.520 --> 40:25.280
Working for a man who's pure evil,
I think I'd do the same.

40:25.280 --> 40:28.120
Which is why I want you to
stay away from him.

40:28.120 --> 40:30.480
And that's why I wanted YOU to help!

40:31.760 --> 40:33.360
Not like this.

40:43.280 --> 40:47.120
What's that, that Yeats poem...

40:48.920 --> 40:50.600
..about it all going to shit?

40:53.400 --> 40:58.200
You're better educated than I am,
Kate, Eve made sure of that.

41:00.600 --> 41:04.640
Well, it's a shame then...

41:06.520 --> 41:08.680
..because only I can know...

41:10.080 --> 41:12.600
..how your centre

41:12.600 --> 41:14.720
couldn't hold.

41:27.880 --> 41:30.040
DOOR SLAMS SHUTS

41:30.040 --> 41:31.560
Tell me about Alice Munezero.

41:34.320 --> 41:36.880
There is a tale of a young prince,
weak and jealous...

41:39.160 --> 41:42.440
..who thought he would make a better
king than his older brother.

41:43.800 --> 41:49.240
So, one day, the old king gave his
sons a bundle of tied sticks

41:49.240 --> 41:52.320
and asked them to break it in half.

41:52.320 --> 41:55.240
But try as they might,
neither could.

41:55.240 --> 41:59.400
So then, the old king cut the cord
and handing out the sticks one

41:59.400 --> 42:04.320
by one, the princes found that they
could snap each, without effort.

42:04.320 --> 42:08.760
"This is the importance of unity,"
the old king told them.

42:08.760 --> 42:12.280
Whereupon the youngest prince,
holding the two halves of a broken

42:12.280 --> 42:17.000
stick plunged each into the heart of
his father and elder brother,

42:17.000 --> 42:18.880
killing them.

42:18.880 --> 42:20.200
And from then on,

42:20.200 --> 42:26.560
the young prince was free to rule
the kingdom alone and uncontested.

42:26.560 --> 42:29.880
For this story to work for
Alice Munezero,

42:29.880 --> 42:32.480
you need only change her gender.

42:33.480 --> 42:35.880
They're sisters?
Of experience, yes.

42:37.000 --> 42:42.440
But, only one knows how to truly
lead a nation - Bibi Mundanzi.

42:43.640 --> 42:45.880
Your president broke her
own promise to your country.

42:45.880 --> 42:47.720
She ran for a third term.

42:47.720 --> 42:52.000
And she was elected by 91%
of the electorate.

42:52.000 --> 42:53.280
And do you know why?

42:53.280 --> 42:56.120
Because everything she does
improves our country.

42:57.360 --> 42:59.960
It was unconstitutional.

42:59.960 --> 43:04.400
The constitution was changed by
95% of the electorate.

43:04.400 --> 43:07.360
And is that how you do things
in your country?

43:07.360 --> 43:09.520
If it doesn't work for you,
you just change the rules?

43:09.520 --> 43:10.960
HE LAUGHS

43:13.120 --> 43:18.200
I believe your country recently made
changes to fixed-term parliaments.

43:18.200 --> 43:20.040
It's what progressive
governments do.

43:20.040 --> 43:22.000
Yours is a dangerous precedent...
No.

43:23.240 --> 43:27.160
A tiny cartel of Western elites,
conspiring to manipulate

43:27.160 --> 43:30.440
international justice,
in an attempt to do what?

43:30.440 --> 43:32.720
What are your friends trying to do?
Who are my friends?

43:32.720 --> 43:33.880
Alice.

43:33.880 --> 43:35.160
Michael Ennis.

43:35.160 --> 43:36.200
Who else?

43:37.400 --> 43:40.920
Looking to destabilise one of the
most forward-thinking states

43:40.920 --> 43:43.800
in the entire African continent!

43:43.800 --> 43:48.040
That is a dangerous precedent!
And that needs to be stopped.

43:48.040 --> 43:49.080
Now.

43:56.680 --> 43:57.960
You know they're lovers.

44:00.680 --> 44:02.600
Then.

44:02.600 --> 44:03.640
And now.

44:06.600 --> 44:08.920
That's not possible.

44:08.920 --> 44:11.240
Except, it is.

44:33.920 --> 44:35.560
Everyone has been lying to you.

44:39.120 --> 44:40.520
Everyone.

44:43.240 --> 44:44.600
You have to help us.

45:25.360 --> 45:26.800
SCREEN UNLOCKS

45:30.120 --> 45:31.360
MOBILE PHONE MAKES CALL

45:33.880 --> 45:37.520
MAN: Hello?
Hi, my name's Kate Ashby.

45:37.520 --> 45:40.040
I believe you may know my mother,
Eve Ashby.

45:40.040 --> 45:41.080
Yeah.

45:41.080 --> 45:43.280
Sorry to hear what happened.

45:43.280 --> 45:45.760
Bad business.

45:45.760 --> 45:51.000
So the reason I'm calling is because
your number is on my mother's mobile
phone and I notice she called you

45:51.000 --> 45:54.080
a couple of days before she died.
Is that right?

45:54.080 --> 45:56.520
Yes. And I was just wondering if you
can remember

45:56.520 --> 45:58.000
what it was she called about.

45:59.120 --> 46:02.480
Oh, she,
she wanted to look at a file.

46:04.760 --> 46:06.800
File? What file?

46:06.800 --> 46:11.880
You and I would need to eye-ball
each other before I told you that.

46:11.880 --> 46:14.120
Why was she asking you for it?

46:14.120 --> 46:16.440
Because I'm the one who's got 'em.

46:16.440 --> 46:18.280
Sorry?

46:18.280 --> 46:20.280
In storage.

46:20.280 --> 46:22.480
You've got...
All the company files, yeah.

46:24.360 --> 46:25.400
Because?

46:25.400 --> 46:28.320
Because, I'm Mark Viner.

46:28.320 --> 46:32.680
I used to be her head of chambers
when she first started out.

46:32.680 --> 46:36.000
Hmm?
When I retired, I closed the firm.

46:36.000 --> 46:39.280
Your mother went on to join
that Ennis fella.

46:39.280 --> 46:41.280
When exactly was that?

46:41.280 --> 46:42.640
December '97.

46:42.640 --> 46:45.520
But up until that time
she was working...

46:45.520 --> 46:46.880
For me, yes.

46:48.720 --> 46:51.200
Sir, if I was to come out
to your house,

46:51.200 --> 46:53.560
would you allow me access
to that file?

46:53.560 --> 46:56.080
You'd have to have legal authority.

46:56.080 --> 46:58.000
I work for my mother's firm.

46:58.000 --> 46:59.760
Then I can't see why not.

47:00.960 --> 47:02.320
Would tonight be too late?

47:19.120 --> 47:20.160
HEAVY RAINFALL

47:38.760 --> 47:40.200
CAR ALARM SYSTEM CHIRPS

47:40.200 --> 47:41.240
THUNDER

47:57.200 --> 47:59.160
SHE GASPS

47:59.160 --> 48:01.720
Ms Ashby? My name is Daniel Drewe.
I'm a solicitor.

48:01.720 --> 48:05.000
No, sorry, I'm in a rush.

48:06.400 --> 48:07.440
Er, could you?

48:11.080 --> 48:13.800
My client requested
that I make contact with you.

48:13.800 --> 48:15.200
He would like to with meet you.

48:15.200 --> 48:17.320
Now, if that's at all possible.

48:18.400 --> 48:20.360
Who's your client?
Patrice Ganimana.

48:22.840 --> 48:24.280
I have a car waiting.

48:28.760 --> 48:30.480
To go where?

48:30.480 --> 48:31.640
Here, in London.

48:34.400 --> 48:36.200
I'll follow.

48:36.200 --> 48:39.960
Forgive me, but I believe you're
the one being followed?

48:39.960 --> 48:43.960
Which represents an unacceptable
risk to my client, again,

48:43.960 --> 48:45.120
on my advice.

48:47.760 --> 48:49.880
It depends on how much he
wants to see me.

48:49.880 --> 48:52.440
No, I'm afraid on this point,
Ms Ashby,

48:52.440 --> 48:56.600
it depends on how much you want to
hear what he has to say.

48:56.600 --> 48:57.960
The car's just over there.

49:25.840 --> 49:27.360
He, he's not in hospital?

49:27.360 --> 49:29.560
He's on rounds of chemotherapy.

49:32.160 --> 49:33.920
He's been freed?

49:33.920 --> 49:35.440
House arrest.

49:35.440 --> 49:37.720
In an embassy?
Friend's house.

49:37.720 --> 49:38.840
On an embassy street?

49:41.000 --> 49:42.160
It's a big house.

50:07.000 --> 50:08.040
Some friends.

50:24.880 --> 50:27.280
I will admit, I'm surprised.

50:27.280 --> 50:28.920
I said I didn't think you'd come.

50:30.120 --> 50:31.400
He said he knew you would.

50:44.320 --> 50:45.360
Please.

52:37.240 --> 52:38.280
Bonsoir.

52:43.760 --> 52:44.880
Je savais que vous...

52:54.720 --> 52:56.040
SHE STIFLES A SOB

53:00.280 --> 53:03.880
You fuck, fucked...

53:03.880 --> 53:05.400
Fucker, you fucker!

53:19.680 --> 53:21.320
HE CONTINUES IN FRENCH

53:46.560 --> 53:47.600
HE SIGHS HEAVILY

53:58.640 --> 53:59.680
Bien sur.

54:02.760 --> 54:04.440
Imbecile!

54:21.000 --> 54:22.120
Penser.

54:47.120 --> 54:49.160
And I did not kill your mother.

54:50.280 --> 54:52.880
You killed Simon Nyamoya?

54:52.880 --> 54:54.240
No.

54:54.240 --> 54:55.960
He was your enemy.

54:55.960 --> 54:57.040
Yes.

54:57.040 --> 54:58.440
You wanted him dead.

54:59.800 --> 55:01.400
Of course.

55:01.400 --> 55:02.480
But it wasn't me.

55:04.160 --> 55:05.800
Someone did it for you.

55:05.800 --> 55:07.720
I did not order it.

55:07.720 --> 55:08.880
It was not me.

55:08.880 --> 55:10.920
And I did not kill your mother.

55:25.280 --> 55:26.320
So?

55:27.440 --> 55:29.160
You want to put me in jail.

55:30.880 --> 55:31.920
Yes! Don't.

55:33.200 --> 55:36.400
You won't. No-one will.

55:36.400 --> 55:37.600
Why not?

55:39.600 --> 55:40.920
I'm already there.

55:42.960 --> 55:49.200
I spend every second of my life
living with what happened.

55:49.200 --> 55:50.440
With what you did?

55:50.440 --> 55:52.160
Every second.

55:52.160 --> 55:53.560
So you admit you're guilty.

55:54.920 --> 55:58.920
I was born at the wrong time,
on the wrong side.

55:58.920 --> 56:02.200
THAT is not what I said.

56:02.200 --> 56:03.960
And I have paid the price.

56:03.960 --> 56:05.520
No.

56:05.520 --> 56:06.920
No, no, no, no, you haven't.

56:08.920 --> 56:10.560
A million people paid the price!

56:11.840 --> 56:13.240
You just have to live with it!

56:13.240 --> 56:17.840
Nothing you could do to me could be
worse than what I already live with.

56:17.840 --> 56:18.880
Not enough.

56:20.040 --> 56:22.320
Nowhere...

56:22.320 --> 56:24.080
..near.

56:24.080 --> 56:26.320
Don't try to put me in jail.

56:26.320 --> 56:30.520
Oh, I'm going to try very,
very hard.

56:31.560 --> 56:33.160
They won't let you.

56:33.160 --> 56:34.400
Who's they?

56:34.400 --> 56:36.680
The people I'm trying to
save you from.

56:36.680 --> 56:40.280
The people who own this? Shouldn't
be too difficult to find out.

56:40.280 --> 56:44.520
Whoever you think owns this
is not who you should be afraid of.

56:45.720 --> 56:47.840
Then who should I be?

56:47.840 --> 56:49.160
They will kill you.

56:50.600 --> 56:53.480
They will kill anyone
who tries to stop them...

56:53.480 --> 56:54.640
From doing what?

56:59.200 --> 57:00.600
Repeating the past.

57:01.640 --> 57:05.280
That's weird, because killing was
so much a part of it!

57:12.160 --> 57:16.080
There, I have saved you.

57:19.800 --> 57:21.400
From what?

57:21.400 --> 57:23.000
Whether you like it or not.

57:23.000 --> 57:24.520
You have nothing on me.

57:24.520 --> 57:28.920
No, you are free
and I cannot follow.

57:30.360 --> 57:33.120
Next time I see you,
you'll be in the dock.

57:34.720 --> 57:39.400
If that should be,
then you won't ever see me again.

57:40.960 --> 57:42.720
God bless you, Kate Ashby.

57:43.800 --> 57:46.120
You still believe all that?

57:46.120 --> 57:48.000
Oh, yes.

57:48.000 --> 57:51.280
It is of Him I am most afraid.
